   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Project Summary (Plain Language)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is this project about?
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We want to find out whether access to high-quality heart imaging services (specifically MRI and CT scans for the
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: heart) is spread fairly across the United States, or if it is concentrated in wealthy, urban areas while poorer, rural
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: communities have little or no access.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is ACR Accreditation?
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The American College of Radiology (ACR) grants a quality stamp of approval (
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: accreditation
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) to imaging facilities
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that meet certain standards. Facilities with this accreditation are recognized by insurance companies as providing
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quality imaging. We are looking ONLY at ACR-accredited facilities in this project.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What will we produce?
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A clean dataset linking every US county with counts of accredited cardiac imaging facilities and
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: socioeconomic/geographic indicators.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A colored map (choropleth) of the US showing where cardiac imaging facilities are concentrated.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A summary table showing how facility access differs by community vulnerability and rural/urban
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: status.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Statistical models measuring the strength of the relationship between community disadvantage and
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: imaging access.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Why does this matter?
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If heart imaging capacity is concentrated in wealthy metro areas, then people in vulnerable communities may not
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:58,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have local access to quality cardiac diagnostics, potentially contributing to worse heart health outcomes.
