   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Step-by-Step Task List
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phase 1: Data Acquisition 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Setup (Day 1)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 1.1 — Set Up Your Project Environment
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Create a Python virtual environment or conda environment for this project.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Install all required libraries (see Section 4 below).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Create a folder structure: 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data/raw/
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data/processed/
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: output/figures/
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: output/tables/
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: code/
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 1.2 — Download External Datasets
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: HUD ZIP-County Crosswalk:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Go to https://www.huduser.gov/portal/datasets/usps
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: crosswalk.html
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Download the ZIP-to-County crosswalk file for Q1 2026 (most recent quarter
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: available).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This file tells you which county each ZIP code belongs to. Some ZIP codes span
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: multiple counties — you will use the one with the largest residential address share
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (column 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RES_RATIO
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CDC SVI:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Go to https://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/placeandhealth/svi/
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Download the 2022 county-level SVI dataset (CSV format).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Important:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Before downloading, check if a 2024 release has been published. If yes,
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confirm with the project lead whether to use 2022 or 2024.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The key column you need is 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RPL_THEMES
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — this is the overall vulnerability
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: percentile rank (0 to 1, where 1 = most vulnerable).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: USDA RUCC:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Go to https://www.ers.usda.gov/data-products/rural-urban-continuum-codes
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Download the 2023 update (Excel file).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The key column is the RUCC code (1–9). Codes 1–3 = metropolitan (urban); codes 4–9 =
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nonmetropolitan (rural).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ACS Population Data:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Use the Census API (you
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll need a free API key from https://api.census.gov/data/key
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signup.html).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pull county-level data for: total population AND population aged 45 years and older.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tables to query: B01001 (Sex by Age) — sum age groups 45+ for both sexes.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Alternatively, download the pre-tabulated data from data.census.gov.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TIGER/Line Shapefiles:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Go to
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: https://www.census.gov/geographies/mapping-files/time-series/geo/tiger-line-file.html
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Download the 2023 county-level shapefile (look for 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Counties (and equivalent)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: under the national file).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This gives you the geographic boundaries needed to draw the map.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 1.3 — Verify All Downloads
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Confirm each file opens correctly.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Check that county FIPS codes are 5 digits (with leading zeros preserved as strings).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Confirm the SVI file covers all ~3,143 US counties.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phase 2: Data Linkage 
