   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (All 2,273 rows qualify.)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Check for expired accreditations:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If the 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Expiration Date
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is before May 20, 2026 (the
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extraction date), exclude that facility. This ensures we only count currently valid accreditations.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Separate into two groups:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cardiac MRI facilities: where 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: modality
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MRAP
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (725 records)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cardiac CT facilities: where 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: modality
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CTAP
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (1,548 records)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Double-counting rule:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If the same facility (same name + same ZIP) appears once for MRI and once
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for CT, that is correct — count it once in each modality
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s total. Do NOT remove it as a duplicate.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ensure all ZIP codes are 5-digit strings (pad with leading zeros if needed, e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 07652
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  not 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 7652
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 2.2 — Map ZIP Codes to County FIPS Codes
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Load the HUD ZIP-County crosswalk file.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For each facility ZIP code, find the corresponding county FIPS code.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Handling multi-county ZIPs:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Some ZIP codes span more than one county. Assign the facility to
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the county with the highest 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RES_RATIO
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (residential address ratio) — this is the county where most
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: residents of that ZIP actually live.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: After this step, every facility should have a 5-digit county FIPS code attached.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Verify: count total facilities per county and confirm the national total still matches (725 MRI +
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1,548 CT = 2,273).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 2.3 — Build the County-Level Analytic Dataset
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Start with a master list of all 3,143 US counties (50 states + DC; exclude US territories like Puerto
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rico, Guam, etc.).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For each county, count:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Number of Cardiac MRI (MRAP) facilities
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Number of Cardiac CT (CTAP) facilities
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Join (merge) the following data onto each county row:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SVI:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RPL_THEMES
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  percentile rank → also create SVI quartile (divide into 4 equal
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: groups: Q1 = least vulnerable, Q4 = most vulnerable).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RUCC:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Code (1–9) → also create a binary variable: Metropolitan = 1 if RUCC 1–3, else 0.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Population:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Total population AND adults aged ≥45.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Calculate rates:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CMR rate = (CMR facility count / adult population ≥45) × 100,000
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CCT rate = (CCT facility count / adult population ≥45) × 100,000
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Create a rate-exclusion flag: if a county has fewer than 1,000 adults aged ≥45, flag it (set 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rate_excluded = 1
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ). These counties still appear in counts but their per-capita rates are
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: excluded from statistical analysis because with so few people the rates would be misleadingly
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extreme.
