   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Calculate Spearman
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s rank correlation between:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CMR rate per 100k and SVI percentile (continuous)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CCT rate per 100k and SVI percentile (continuous)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Report the correlation coefficient (rho) and the p-value.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What this tells us:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A negative correlation means that as vulnerability increases, imaging access
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decreases (the expected disparity pattern).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phase 4: Choropleth Map (Days 2–3)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 4.1 — Prepare Map Data
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Load the TIGER/Line county shapefile.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Merge your analytic dataset (from Task 2.4) onto the shapefile using the county FIPS code.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Verify all counties have geometry data attached.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 4.2 — Create Figure 1 (Two-Panel Choropleth)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Build a map with two panels:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Panel A:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Cardiac MRI facilities per 100,000 adults ≥45, by county.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Panel B:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Cardiac CT facilities per 100,000 adults ≥45, by county.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Map specifications:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Layout:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Panels stacked vertically (A on top, B below) — recommended for journal portrait format.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Color scheme:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Sequential blue palette (light blue → dark blue). Use 5 bins for counties WITH
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: facilities, plus:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Light gray = counties with zero facilities
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: White = counties excluded from rate calculation (adult ≥45 population 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1,000)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Binning method:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Quantile-based (each bin has roughly the same number of counties). Also try
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: natural-breaks (Jenks) as an alternative for comparison.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Map projection:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Albers USA composite projection (standard for US thematic maps). Show Alaska
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and Hawaii as insets at their own appropriate scale — do NOT stretch Alaska to lower-48 scale.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Boundaries:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  State boundaries = thin dark gray lines. County boundaries = very thin light gray lines.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Annotation:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Add a note box in the lower-right corner explaining exclusions and color scheme.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Output format:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Save as PDF (vector, preferred) AND PNG (minimum 600 dpi as backup).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 4.3 — Write the Figure Legend
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Include this draft legend (to be finalized by the project lead):
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Figure 1. Geographic distribution of ACR-accredited cardiac imaging capacity by US county.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Choropleth maps show the number of facilities accredited by the American College of Radiology for
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (A) Cardiac MRI and (B) Cardiac CT, per 100,000 adults aged ≥45 years, by county. Color intensity
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: indicates facility density (quantile-binned). Light gray indicates counties with zero accredited
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: facilities. White indicates counties excluded from rate calculation due to small adult population.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: County boundaries derived from US Census TIGER/Line 2023 shapefiles. Alaska and Hawaii are
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shown as insets and are not to scale.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phase 5: Statistical Modeling (Day 3)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 5.1 — Negative Binomial Regression (Primary Model)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is this?
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A type of statistical model used when counting things (like number of facilities) where the data is 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: overdispersed
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (the spread is wider than a simple Poisson model would predict).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Model setup:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Outcome (what we
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re predicting):
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Facility count per county (run separately for CMR and CCT).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Main predictor:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SVI percentile, scaled per 10-percentile increment (so multiply the 0–1 score by 10
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to get 0–10 scale, or divide by 0.1).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Offset:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  log(adult population ≥45). This converts the model from predicting raw counts to predicting
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rates.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What to report:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Incidence Rate Ratio (IRR) with 95% confidence interval. An IRR 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 means
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fewer facilities as vulnerability increases.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Steps:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fit a Poisson model first.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fit a negative binomial model.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compare AIC (Akaike Information Criterion) — lower is better. The negative binomial should fit better
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: if there is overdispersion.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Report the dispersion parameter from the negative binomial model.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Run separately for CMR and CCT.
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Task 5.2 — Sensitivity Analyses
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Run these additional models to check if results are robust:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Exclude 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Under Review
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  facilities:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Re-run using only the 2,250 
