   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Accredited
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  facilities (drop the
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 23 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Under Review
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SVI as quartiles:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Instead of using SVI as a continuous number, replace it with 4 indicator (dummy)
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: variables for quartiles Q2, Q3, Q4 (Q1 is the reference group).
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stratified by rurality:
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Run the regression separately for metropolitan counties only, then for
   DEBUG: 2026-05-22 16:29:59,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nonmetropolitan counties only.
